Version 0.1.4

- Adds parameter "collection_name" to the MongoDB backend. With this, you can run different experiments in parallel and
store the twits in different collections


Version 0.1.3

- Added backend for MongoDB: Stores the whole JSON blob for the tweet, no defined fields


Version 0.1.2

- Added --exclude-replies option, to skip tweets that are replies to other users
- Add type annotations and formatting checking
- Added --extended-text option, to fetch the full tweet text
- Fixes a bug that made the option --exclude-quotes to not work